With Esther besides me,
I set up all the lenses.
Heart was bumping
Hands were sweating
Smile was showed up on my face
We were waiting for you to step on the stage
To start dancing

This was the night when the sun showed up in the night
So bright
So dazzling

This was the night when the audience clapped so loud
This was the night when we won the competition
This was the night when we celebrated our winning

This was the night
This was the night
This was the night that I would never forget.

I didn't need to be on the stage to feel as happy as you are
Because our coach told us to have the same heartbeat the moment you step on the stage

So I always count when you were counting on the stage
I always sing when the musicians were singing
I always stomp my feet to get the beat
Therefore, it was easy to feel what you felt back then

Cause your heartbeat is my heartbeat too.

caption.text:
(1/2)
I came here as a crew. Maybe some people (maybe you too) would think why I chose to be a crew instead of to be a musician, but I found my reason.
-

It was so so sad when some of you were sick. Because deep inside I want we do the best in all of our performances but the fact is I can do nothing. I am not a musician nor a dancer.

This feeling of powerlessness and uselessness taught me to keep praying, asking Him to make me as useful as I can here, til I know my part in this team. -
To be your mirror to help you all see your own movement
To be your legs when you need it
To be your personal carer when you are sick
To be your eyes to capture your moments there

I can be anything and I can do anything to keep you all as healthy as possible, to make us give our best performances, and to keep us shining brighter more and more.

I love to do these things for you all, this is not that I just did what I must to do as a crew. I just love you guys that much (meskipun kadang suka sebel krn disuruh potoin mele kek personal fotografer hehehehe).
.
I wish you had a good time with me  there, because I had :) Selamat untuk kita, sang juara dunia.

Sweet Child Of Mine
by Stephanie Dunne

Tonight I'll sing you a lullaby 
Sweet Child of Mine

I'll settle you down in this Earth 
With trouble, joy, sorrow, love and laughter 
Each path holds a different key 
To your destiny 
Sweet Child of Mine

If you have trouble 
I'll carry you to laughter 
If you have joy 
I'll sing your way to love 
And if you have sorrow just give me a call 
I'll be there right beside you 
Sweet Child of Mine

So take life by the wings 
And fly swiftly through each course 
Cauz you'll find life is a lesson 
Meant to be learned

Sweet Child of Mine
.
.
.

hari itu kita berjumpa lagi

bagi aku yang dicekat kenang
ingin rasanya kuhadirkan senja yang pernah seindah kamu
supaya bisa kuberikan lagi yang selalu mempesonamu

caption.text:
A True Account Of Talking To The Sun On Fire Island by Frank O'Hara

The Sun woke me this morning loud
and clear, saying "Hey! I've been
trying to wake you up for fifteen
minutes. Don't be so rude, you are
only the second poet I've ever chosen
to speak to personally

so why
aren't you more attentive? If I could
burn you through the window I would
to wake you up. I can't hang around
here all day."
.
"Sorry, Sun, I stayed
up late last night talking to Hal." "When I woke up Mayakovsky he was
a lot more prompt" the Sun said
petulantly. "Most people are up
already waiting to see if I'm going
to put in an appearance."
.
I tried
to apologize "I missed you yesterday."
"That's better" he said. "I didn't
know you'd come out." "You may be
wondering why I've come so close?"
"Yes" I said beginning to feel hot
wondering if maybe he wasn't burning me
anyway.
.
"Frankly I wanted to tell you
I like your poetry. I see a lot
on my rounds and you're okay. You may
not be the greatest thing on earth, but
you're different. Now, I've heard some
say you're crazy, they being excessively
calm themselves to my mind, and other
crazy poets think that you're a boring
reactionary. Not me.

Just keep on
like I do and pay no attention. You'll
find that people always will complain
about the atmosphere, either too hot
or too cold too bright or too dark, days
too short or too long.

If you don't appear
at all one day they think you're lazy
or dead. Just keep right on, I like it.

And don't worry about your lineage
poetic or natural. The Sun shines on
the jungle, you know, on the tundra
the sea, the ghetto. Wherever you were
I knew it and saw you moving. I was waiting
for you to get to work.

And now that you
are making your own days, so to speak,
even if no one reads you but me
you won't be depressed. Not
everyone can look up, even at me. It
hurts their eyes."
"Oh Sun, I'm so grateful to you!" "Thanks and remember I'm watching.
Visit to continue: https://m.poemhunter.com/poem/a-true-account-of-talking-to-the-sun-on-fire-isl/

caption.text:
To the friend who has ever wondered why I imagine her as a forest big tree. Here is the story behind it.

It was cold, very cold. 
12°C in summer felt so wrong for me, however it was relaxing too as the wind blowing my face.

As long as I remember, I was in my journey to Austria and we went through the forest to be there. When we went through the forest, I started to wonder "oh, what would old-forest-big trees say if they were alive?" .
-
In my imagination, I think they would tell me stories that I have never heard before, knowledge, and things about life, bad or good, since they have been here for a long long time and have a capacity to be wiser than others.
-
It was just like you, the one who often blurt out a practical knowledge while we were talking, ensiklopedia berjalan emang. A good listener, dan orang yang mengayomi diantara kita ber 4. I am very grateful for knowing you this year, be friend, done and learned many things together, I hope you had a good time too while we're together heheh.
.
.

caption.text:
Balwana

Balwana dalam bahasa Sansekerta berarti akar. Akar yang tertanam dengan dalam menjadi awal kehidupan dan berperan sebagai penguat. Tidak sedikit halangan dalam jalannya untuk bertumbuh. Namun dengan akar yang kuat , makhluk hidup akan bertahan dan tidak rubuh. Tarian ini menggambarkan keadaan manusia yang pada dasarnya memiliki jiwa yang putih.
.
Akan tetapi, lingkungan terkadang 
menggoyahkan manusia sehingga manusia menyimpang dari norma. Oleh sebab itu, dibutuhkan sebuah pemberontakan dari manusia lain untuk menyuarakan kebenaran.
.
Pada akhirnya manusia dapat berjalan bersama dalam kebenaran tersebut. Karena sesungguhnya manusia pun memiliki akar. Manusia akan kembali pada akarnya, pada hakikatnya, yaitu kebaikan yang abadi.

caption.text:
#Day18 -
[Kemanapun kita berjalan, jangan pernah lupa untuk berinteraksi dengan penduduk lokal]
-
Jadi begitu tiba kami mampir dulu di rumah Kapolsek Kurulu yg merupakan tulang dari sepupu saya. Kemudian kami diantar ke Kurulu untuk melihat mummy Jiwika ini.
-
Mummy tersebut berumur 369 tahun, dilihat dari tali yg diikatkan di lehernya setiap 5 thn sekali. Yonas (baju merah) merupakan keturunan dr mummy itu. Berkat bantuan tulang Kapolsek Kurulu itu kami bisa foto bersama 25 orang dari mereka.
-
Foto bersama mereka dan melihat mummy biasanya dikenakan biaya yg mahal, tapi untuk kami biaya yg keluar sebesar Rp450.000,00. -
Tidak hanya itu di sana mrk juga menjual aksesoris sprt kalung dr taring babi seharga Rp450.000,00 dan barang lainnya.

Jadi inilah perbatasan antara Papua kita dengan Papua New Guinea/Papua Nugini (PNG). Di sini panasnya panas banget lebih panas dari pantai. Untuk sampai ke sini kita harus lewat pemeriksaan dulu di semacam pos darurat begitu brp kilometer sebelum sampai, krn daerah ini lumayan rawan karena ada gerakan OPM. #Day10 [Udang Rumah Laut]

Makan malam di sini, suasananya memang enak. Tempatnya tepat di atas laut, tapi kita bisa liat gunung juga di depan mata penuh lampu lampu. Jayapura memang di antara gunung dan laut, jadi makan di sini kita bisa liat keduanya. 
Selesai makan saya mau melihat lihat suasana laut, ketika saya melihat ke bawah laut ternyata ada hiu. Hiu itu dalam keramba.

#Day4
[Mengenang Persipura]
Location: Stadion Mandala Jayapura

Jadi tadi sore kami jalan ke sini untuk olahraga. Dari kemarin sudah lihat stadionnya dari atas, bagus memang dan ketika td masuk untungnya tidak kecewa, memang sesuai yg kemarin dilihat. 
Stadion ini dulunya dipakai Persipura untuk latihan, tapi sayang sekarang Persipura sudah dibubarkan. Meskipun begitu stadion ini masih ramai digunakan, tadi pun banyak atlet lari yg sedang latihan di sini. Meskipun Persipura sudah dibubarkan lapangan sepakbola di sini tetap tidak boleh digunakan untuk umum, kata seorang bapa setelah penjaga stadion memarahi beberapa org yg bermain di tengah.

caption.text:
#Day2 (4/4) [Pantai 100ribu]
Location: sebenarnya kurang tau pantai apa, dari Pantai Base G belok kanan lurus terus hampir ujung.

Jadi kenapa judulnya seperti itu ada ceritanya. Habis puas di pantai base G yg tadi kami ceritanya mau explore lagi, kata bapa "iyo tra papa ke sana", jadilah kami jalan.

Begitu sampai ada seorang mama sedang menyapu pasir pantai dekat pondok, tapi kami tak dipungut uang. Foto fotolah kami di situ, karena airnya lebih berwarna tosca dibanding yg tadi. Pantai ini juga bnyk batu besarnya di ujungnya, kira kira setinggi 3 meter. 
Puas foto foto saudara saya ceritanya mau kasih mama itu Rp5000, sama dengan pantai tadi. Tiba-tiba mama itu minta uang parkir 100ribu. Ageee (aduh), saya di pondok tak berani lihat hanya berdoa saja supaya gak diapa apain. Saudara saya kasih Rp20.000 lagi, blg tak punya uang. Mama itu cemberut masih sambil menyapu tak mau membuka tangannya untuk menerima.

Sempat agak kesal sedikit, pas dibilang "demi Tuhan" kalau kami gak punya uang barulah dngn terpaksa diterima.

Jadi di sini orang bisa punya pantai sendiri.

caption.text:
#Day2 (3/4)
[Mengabadikan Pantai Base G]

Mama bilang Bapa itu yang punya pantai ini.
"Dia yang pu pantai ini, tapi dia sedikit tuli. Kasih keras e kalau ko ngomong" begitulah pesan mama kira-kira. "Bapa panggil sa kah?" Kata saya sambil jalan namun tidak direspon, sepertinya tidak dengar. Kemudian saya sampai di sampingnya, sambil berdiri menanyakan hal yang sama dalam hati sedikit cemas entah kenapa.Tiba-tiba saya dibuat bingung oleh Bapa itu. "Ko di sini foto-foto untuk apa?" Deg. Saya langsung takut dimarahi atau diminta uang banyak karena katanya org sini suka begitu. "Aaa, sa hanya foto-foto saja Bapa tidak untuk apa-apa" tapi sepertinya bapa itu tidak mendengar. "Ko pasang harga ko pu foto berapa satu lembar? Nanti ko cetak, ko kasih saya nanti sa bayar, sa beli to." Saya bingung setengah mati, seumur-umur belum pernah ditanya begitu. 
Kemudian topik berganti setelah saudara saya jelaskan, saya foto untuk tugas sekolah bukan untuk cari uang. Bapa itu cerita dulu orang banyak ke sana, tapi sekarang sudah sepi. Bapa itu yang bikin semua pondok di pantai ini pakai biaya sendiri tanpa dibantu pemerintah, dengan biaya masuk hanya Rp 5000.
